The shelf life of platelet concentrates (PCs) was limited in Germany to 4 days 
after the day of production because platelet-related septic complications had 
been observed, mainly with PCs at the end of their shelf life. The reduction in 
PC shelf life gives rise to several problems, including an increased number of 
discarded products, accompanied by potential challenges of how to ensure an 
adequate supply of platelet products. The aim of this study was to show routine 
experience over the last 7 years using the Bactiflow (BF) assay to screen for 
bacterial contamination late in PC storage, followed by extension of PC shelf 
